indicator("Weinstein & Swing Pro Dashboard [v67.4.13]", overlay=true, max_bars_back=5000, max_lines_count=500)

// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.13 (2026-06-01) — Decision-Mode prospective Gate-3 R:R preview
// ==========================================
// Display-only: the compact "LEVELS / ROOM" row now appends a prospective R:R
// estimate (setupRRStr) for setups with NO entry profile set (finalEntry == 0),
// where the active-trade "Current R:R" row never fires. Estimate uses
// entry = close, SL = close − 2.5 × ATR(14) (14-day ATR stop methodology),
// reward = distance to nearest overhead level (ovhPrice); "~" prefix marks it
// as an estimate, "open ▲" when no overhead level (blue-sky). Pure display —
// does NOT create/modify any entry/SL profile and does NOT touch RRG logic.
//
// Also: direction arrows in WEEKLY / DAILY / 50DMA / RRG / ATH rows switched
// from thin text glyphs (↗ ↘ ↔ → ↑ ↓) to emoji-variation arrows
// (↗️ ↘️ ↔️ ➡️ ⬆️ ⬇️) so they render as the clearly-visible blue-square icons
// already used by the RS (vs N500/Sec) row. GLYPH-ONLY — no threshold or RRG
// calculation logic changed; only the rendered character differs.
//
// Also: "Data Size" input default raised size.small → size.normal (data text +
// icons render larger for readability); size.large added as an option. Section
// sub-headers (ACT NOW / STRUCTURE / CONTEXT / PORTFOLIO and the title) stay
// fixed at size.normal — deliberately NOT enlarged, per request.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.12 (2026-05-24) — Bearish detectors neutralized to Tier 0
// ==========================================
// N500 × 5y regime-split validation (PA_FIELD_VALIDATION_v3) measured the
// four bearish "warning" detectors as ALL predicting the wrong direction
// in BOTH regimes (predictive alpha = bench_ret - stock_ret):
//
//   Detector              Bull α    Bear α    n         P(α>0)
//   DISTRIBUTION_DAY      -1.67%    -1.56%    51,881    0%
//   SHOOTING_STAR_RESIST  -2.38%    -0.78%    3,732     0%
//   FAILED_BREAKOUT       -2.30%    -1.36%    748       0%
//   BEAR_ENGULF           (not in validator's DETECTORS — same family)
//
// These patterns do NOT predict underperformance — they're regime-
// independent anti-signals over 5 years of N500 data. The traditional-
// TA Tier -2 assignment was convention, never validated; the cascade was
// actively penalizing the Action Signal score on bars that didn't deserve
// the penalty.
//
// CHANGE — all four moved from Tier -2 to Tier 0:
//   * Tier value: -2 -> 0  (no Action Signal score impact)
//   * Label: append " (Watch)" — still visually flagged for human pattern
//     recognition, but no longer scored as warnings
//   * Color: red -> orange/grey
//   * Cascade position: moved from TOP of cascade (positions 1-4) to
//     just before NORMAL default catch-all. This means co-firing bullish
//     states now WIN priority (previously bearish state would override).
//
// REVERSAL CRITERION (documented for future regime check):
// If CRSLDX (Nifty 500 benchmark) trades below its 200-day SMA for 90+
// consecutive days (sustained bear regime), re-run validation and
// reconsider re-activating Tier -2. The current dataset is dominated
// by bull regime; bearish predictive power may emerge in true bear
// markets that we haven't measured.
//
// ==========================================
// PRICE ACTION FIELD — TIMEFRAME GUIDANCE (added 2026-05-24)
// ==========================================
// The PA cascade is VALIDATED ON DAILY TIMEFRAME ONLY. All Tier values,
// alpha numbers, and detector tunings (v67.4.5 -> v67.4.11) come from
// N500 × 5y backtests on DAILY bars. See:
//   PA_FIELD_VALIDATION_v4_nifty500_20260524_133146.md
//
// MTF behavior on intraday charts (75-min / 125-min):
//   * Daily/weekly anchored references (dMA50, dMA200, dLockH, stageID,
//     wMA30, wRSI) STILL render correctly via request.security — these are
//     fetched from their native TF regardless of chart TF
//   * Candle-pattern detectors (pa_hammer, pa_nr7, pa_bull_engulf,
//     pa_vcp_bo, pa_outside_bull, pa_3bar_rev, etc.) fire on CHART-TF bars.
//     On 75-min chart, "pa_hammer" = 75-min hammer, not daily hammer.
//   * Validated daily alpha numbers DO NOT TRANSFER to intraday firings.
//   * No free data source provides 5y of native 75/125-min NSE data:
//       yfinance: no native 75/125, max 730d for 60m
//       Dhan API: 5 days only on intraday
//       TradingView: ~3 months only on 75-min for typical NSE stocks
//     True MTF intraday validation requires paid data vendor or live
//     forward accumulation. Parked as future work.
//
// RECOMMENDED WORKFLOW:
//   * Use DAILY chart for setup discovery — Action Signal score reflects
//     validated tier values, alpha rankings are trustworthy
//   * Use 75-min / 125-min for ENTRY TIMING — read raw price action
//     against the daily structure shown by dMA50, dLockH, stageID, etc.
//     Don't rely on intraday PA state's tier value for the score.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.11 (2026-05-24) — BULL_ENGULF quality gate (B6)
// ==========================================
// N500 × 5y regime-split validation showed pa_bull_engulf delivered
// excellent alpha in BEAR regime (+2.93%, n=283, CI95=(+1.6, +4.4)) but
// near-zero in BULL regime (-0.21%, n=354, CI95=(-1.0, +0.7)). The
// detector was too permissive — capturing normal pullbacks in uptrends
// rather than genuine capitulation reversals.
//
// Multi-variant tightening test (verify_bull_engulf_tightening.py) found
// the WINNING combination = stronger volume + oversold context:
//
//   Variant       Bull α    Bear α    Verdict
//   B1 (pullback) -0.40%    +3.33%    rejected (worse in bull)
//   B2 (vol>2x)   +0.63%    +6.48%    good
//   B3 (deep trd) -0.07%    +3.21%    marginal
//   B4 (RSI<40)   -0.06%    +3.12%    marginal
//   B5 (B2 cap B3) +0.85%   +6.48%    better
//   B6 (B2 cap B4) +1.35%   +6.92%    WINNER
//
// B6 raises both regimes to positive alpha (P(alpha>0) = 91% bull / 100%
// bear) while keeping Tier +2 status. Filter drops ~87% of firings,
// leaving the top 13% highest-conviction setups. Matches classic TA:
// engulfing AT oversold WITH institutional volume = capitulation reversal.
//
// CHANGE:
//   v67.4.10:  pa_bull_engulf = _raw_bull_engulf AND _inDowntrendCtx
//                              AND curRelVol > 1.2
//   v67.4.11:  pa_bull_engulf = _raw_bull_engulf AND _inDowntrendCtx
//                              AND curRelVol > 2.0
//                              AND ta.rsi(close, 14)[1] < 40
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.10 (2026-05-24) — Data-driven OUTSIDE_BAR_BULL demotion
// ==========================================
// N500 × 5y validation (PA_FIELD_VALIDATION_v2_nifty500_20260524_092957.md)
// measured per-state predictive alpha. Tier +2 detectors should deliver
// meaningfully more alpha than Tier +1 to justify the higher priority slot.
// Observed ranking among Tier +2 members:
//   POCKET_PIVOT     +2.10% (n=38,805)
//   UNDERCUT_50SMA   +2.04% (n=7,066)
//   HAMMER_AT_200SMA +1.34% (n=331)
//   BULL_ENGULF      +1.19% (n=739)
//   THREE_BAR_REV    +1.05% (n=6,455)
//   HAMMER_AT_50SMA  +0.83% (n=534)
//   IB_NR7_COIL      +0.58% (n=31,903)
//   OUTSIDE_BAR_BULL +0.46% (n=11,205)   <-- weakest Tier +2
// Tier +1 detectors:
//   HAMMER_REVERSAL  +0.70% (n=18,137)   <-- BEATS OUTSIDE_BAR_BULL
// OUTSIDE_BAR_BULL underperforms a Tier +1 baseline and is the only Tier +2
// detector whose alpha doesn't materially separate from the Tier +1 cluster.
// Action: demote to Tier +1 (still flagged with ★ as a notable pattern, but
// no longer earns the higher slot in the Action Signal score).
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.9 (2026-05-24) — TWO DETECTOR DESIGN-BUG FIXES
// ==========================================
// Universe survey (10 N100 symbols × 5y data, via pa_field_validator.py)
// revealed two detectors firing ZERO times in BOTH Pine and Python:
//
//   FIX #1: pa_vcp_bo — vcp_ok required CURRENT-bar contraction, but the
//     breakout bar IS the expansion bar (close>10dHigh, wide range, vol
//     spike). atr10 spikes on that bar, making atr10<atr40*0.75 false on
//     the same bar where breakout conditions become true. Mathematically
//     antithetical. Fix: vcp_ok now checks PRIOR contraction window
//     (any of the previous 5 bars had atr10 < atr40 * 0.75). The breakout
//     bar itself is the expansion; we want EVIDENCE of contraction BEFORE.
//
//   FIX #2: pa_failed_bo — required close[1] > dLockH, but dLockH = rolling
//     max over last N bars INCLUDING close[1]. So close[1] can EQUAL dLockH
//     (when it WAS the new high) but never strictly exceed it. Impossible
//     condition. Fix: use dLockH[1] (yesterday's locked high, before today
//     could have updated the rolling max).
//
// Both bugs were carried into Weinstein_PA_Field_Strategy_v1.0.pine and
// pa_field_validator.py — fixed in lockstep across all three files.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.8 (2026-05-24) — Hammer-at-MA + 50SMA Undercut & Rally
// ==========================================
// Two additions targeting the most reliable institutional support behaviors.
//
//   1. ★ HAMMER AT 50/200 SMA — promotes plain hammer (Tier +1) to Tier +2
//      when the wick rejects off a major moving average. Tag identifies
//      which MA was defended:
//        • Hammer + low within 1.5% of dMA50 + close > dMA50  → "(at 50SMA)"
//        • Hammer + low within 2.0% of dMA200 + close > dMA200 → "(at 200SMA)"
//      Requires curRelVol > 1.0 — institutional defense leaves a footprint.
//      The plain HAMMER (Tier +1) branch still catches hammers that aren't
//      at a major MA but are in downtrend context.
//
//   2. ★ 50SMA UNDERCUT & RALLY — Tier +2. Distinct from Wyckoff Spring
//      (which keys off the 50-bar low). This detector keys off the 50-day
//      SMA itself — the institutional reference level:
//        • low < dMA50  (intraday undercut)
//        • close > dMA50  (reclaim by close)
//        • close > open  (green bar)
//        • curRelVol > 1.25  (defense volume)
//      Sits above POCKET PIVOT in cascade — when both fire, the undercut
//      is the more specific, more actionable signal.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.7 (2026-05-24) — Base-count tier adjustment + Volume tag
// ==========================================
// Two post-cascade decorators. Both run AFTER the HTF override so they see
// the final paState/paTier and can modify them coherently.
//
//   1. BASE-COUNT TIER ADJUSTMENT (Minervini late-stage discipline)
//      Stage-2 bases #1-2 are highest-probability entries. By base #3 the
//      stock has had two impulse legs; B3 is "late cycle" and B4+ is "very
//      extended." This decorator demotes breakout-class tiers when baseCount
//      is elevated, regardless of how clean the pattern looks:
//        • baseCount == 3  → tier −1, append " ⚠ Late Stage"
//        • baseCount >= 4  → tier −2, append " ⚠ V.Late (B<n>)"
//      Applies only to bullish breakout/launch states (paTier ≥ 2 AND state
//      contains "BREAKOUT" / "LAUNCH"). Defensive patterns (Spring, Hammer,
//      Pocket Pivot at base) are untouched — they're not stage-dependent.
//      HTF override (Tier +4) is exempt: a true HTF is the launch leg, not
//      a late-cycle continuation.
//
//   2. VOLUME-CONFIRMATION TAG (institutional-footprint at a glance)
//      Appends " (Vol+)" / " (Vol++)" / " (Low Vol)" to actionable patterns
//      (|paTier| >= 1) based on curRelVol bucket:
//        • curRelVol >= 2.0  → " (Vol++)"   institutional
//        • curRelVol >= 1.5  → " (Vol+)"    confirmed
//        • curRelVol <  0.7  → " (Low Vol)" warning (esp. for breakouts)
//      Patterns whose definition ALREADY requires vol (Gap-Up BO, Pocket
//      Pivot, Power Play, Distribution) still get the tag — it shows HOW
//      MUCH vol, not just yes/no. NORMAL tier 0 untouched.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.6 (2026-05-24) — Price Action: new patterns + base count
// ==========================================
// Five additions to the PA cascade. Cascade ordering preserved; all new
// detectors slotted by tier severity.
//
//   1. ★ SHOOTING STAR (at Resistance) — bearish mirror of hammer. Tier -2.
//      Body in lower third, upper wick > 2× body, near 52w high or above
//      dMA50 by >15%. Fires only with prior uptrend context.
//
//   2. ★ OUTSIDE BAR (Bullish Engulf+) — Tier +2. high>high[1] AND low<low[1]
//      AND close > high[1]. Stronger than bullish engulfing because it sweeps
//      both prior extremes; gets its own state instead of being absorbed.
//
//   3. ★ GAP-UP BREAKOUT — Tier +3. open > high[1] AND close > dLockH AND
//      volConfirm. Minervini's "exhaustion gap inverse" — institutional
//      footprint. Placed above isTrueBreakout so it earns the +3 it deserves.
//
//   4. ★ IB-NR7 COIL — Tier +2 (promoted from +1 each). When inside bar AND
//      NR7 fire on the same bar, the volatility compression is institutional-
//      grade. Crabel-style coil. Promoted above plain Inside-3 / NR7.
//
//   5. BASE COUNT annotation — tracks number of completed bases since the
//      last Stage 1→2 transition. Base completes when price reclaims prior
//      base-high after a ≥7% pullback. Appended to VCP BO and Stage-2 Launch
//      state strings (e.g. "★ VCP BREAKOUT [B3]"). Third-stage+ bases are
//      late-cycle warnings — the count surfaces it without changing tier.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.5 (2026-05-24) — Price Action audit fixes
// ==========================================
// Audit of the Price Action cascade (lines ~2734-2917) surfaced false-signal
// risks. This patch hardens the detectors without changing the cascade order.
//
// CRITICAL fixes:
//   1. FAILED BREAKOUT — added 0.5×ATR overshoot threshold + relVol gate.
//      Previously fired on any 0.01% wick above dLockH followed by a red close.
//   2. DISTRIBUTION DAY — now compares close vs PRIOR CLOSE (-0.2%) with
//      volume > prior bar's volume (IBD definition). Was using close < open,
//      which could fire on an up-day with a red body.
//   3. STAGE-2 LAUNCH — moved to weekly request.security() so close[1] truly
//      means previous weekly bar. Daily-TF zig-zag around wMA30 no longer
//      repeatedly fires the +3 catalyst.
//
// HIGH-priority hardening:
//   4. POCKET PIVOT — added "above 50-SMA" gate + close in upper half (per
//      Minervini / Bonde). Stops Tier +2 prints inside Stage 4 relief rallies.
//   5. WYCKOFF SPRING — lookback widened 20d→50d + requires light-volume
//      undercut (volume < 50-SMA). Removes most false +3 prints.
//   6. HAMMER — replaced inverted "close > dMA50" filter with proper
//      downtrend-context gate. Hammers now fire where they matter (reversal
//      after a decline) instead of being suppressed below dMA50.
//   7. BULLISH ENGULFING — now requires curRelVol > 1.2 AND downtrend context.
//   8. POWER PLAY (Strong Close) — added curRelVol > 1.0 requirement.
//   9. NR7 — strict-inequality fix: ties on prior bars no longer kill NR7.
//
// Architectural addition:
//   • Helper `_inDowntrendCtx` — used by hammer + bullish engulfing.
//     `close < ta.ema(close,10) and ta.ema(close,10) < ta.ema(close,20)`.
//     Single source of truth for reversal-pattern preconditions.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.4 (2026-05-20) — Ecosystem-wide parity confirmation
// ==========================================
// All sister tools now use the same JdK 1-pass formula, +2-LEADING score, and
// cell-level tradeable rule:
//   • Pine Dashboard v67.4.4  (this file)
//   • Pine Ecosystem strategy v3.1
//   • Pine Bull Screener v3.2  (POS-ACCUM disabled, JdK + +2/0 score)
//   • Pine Recovery Screener v2.0 Wyckoff  (Spring/SOS/JAC catalysts added)
//   • Python bull_screener.py v1.7
//   • Python recovery_screener.py v3.0 (Wyckoff)
//
// No code changes in this dashboard — version bump tracks the consistency.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.3 (2026-05-20) — Recalibrated RRG score after Strike switch
// ==========================================
// AFTER switching to Strike-matched JdK (v67.4.2), the RS-Ratio-side spread
// dropped from 2.71pp → 0.93pp (n=5,020). Per-quadrant data:
//   LEADING   +1.24% (only quadrant with material alpha)
//   IMPROVING +0.07% · WEAKENING +0.07% · LAGGING +0.06% (all flat)
// New score: +2 if LEADING else 0 (was +5/-5 binary).
// New tradeable: cell-level whitelist of (current, next) trajectory pairs:
//   TRUE only for LEADING→LEADING, LEADING→IMPROVING, IMPROVING→LEADING,
//   LAGGING→IMPROVING, WEAKENING→LEADING. All other cells FALSE.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.2 (2026-05-20) — Strike.Money-matched JdK formula
// ==========================================
// Calibration against 15 symbols vs Strike.Money's published values showed:
//   2-pass StockCharts default: ratio err 8.86, quadrant agreement 66.7%
//   1-pass + 5-bar smooth:      ratio err 5.52, quadrant agreement 93.8%
// Strike evidently uses single-pass normalization with final 5-bar smoothing.
// Default jdkLength raised 10 → 12.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.1 — Validated RRG Score (+5/-5) [SUPERSEDED by v67.4.3]
// ==========================================
// VALIDATION: Universe-wide bucketing test (n=5,460, Nifty 500 × 12 anchors,
// no screener filters) killed the 12-cell trajectory matrix (r=0.086 only,
// several cells inverted — e.g. IMPROVING→LEADING +10 score was -0.96% alpha
// at n=154, opposite of the small-sample Nifty 100 read).
//
// SIMPLIFIED SCORE: Replaced the matrix with a single binary signal.
//   RS-Ratio >= 100: +5  (n=2,776, +2.07% mean 30d alpha)
//   RS-Ratio <  100: -5  (n=2,684, -0.64% mean 30d alpha)
// 2.71 pp spread — only RRG signal that survived larger sample.
// NOTE: This calibration was on 2-pass formula; superseded by v67.4.3 after
// switching to Strike-matched 1-pass formula (smaller absolute spread).
//
// NEW: f_rrg_tradeable() — entry-timing gate distinct from the ranking Score.
// Uses quadrant + trajectory + distance from RS-Ratio centerline. Answers
// "OK to buy this stock right now?" Dashboard RS cell now turns RED when
// the stock is in a bullish quadrant BUT trajectory is rapidly rotating into
// a worse one near the centerline (e.g. LEADING with RS-Ratio=100.5 ↘).
// Display: "RRG L (LEADING (stable), +5 · ✓ BUY OK)" or "✗ WAIT" tag.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.4.0 — JdK RRG (StockCharts-default) + Rotation Trajectory
// ==========================================
// PARITY: Migrates RS engine from single-pass Mansfield to JdK 2-pass
// RS-Ratio / RS-Momentum (length=10, no extra smoothing). Matches Bull
// Screener Python v1.5 and Strike.Money / StockCharts RRG conventions.
//
// NEW — RRG trajectory: 4-week velocity vector on the RRG plane projects the
// next likely quadrant. Dashboard RS row now shows e.g.
//   "N500: 5.27 Weakening ↘ · Sec: ... · RRG W (LEADING → WEAKENING)"
// Cell color flips to ORANGE when LEADING is rotating toward WEAKENING
// (or IMPROVING toward LAGGING), and to BLUE on bullish rotations
// (IMPROVING → LEADING, LAGGING → IMPROVING).
//
// CALL SITES: f_calc_rs_logic signature now takes (rsl, rslLevel, slopeLen,
// jdkLen, trailLen) and returns 6 values (added val_trail, mom_trail for
// trajectory). Three request.security call sites updated.
//
// INPUTS ADDED: jdkLength (10), rrgTrailLen (4).
// LEGACY INPUTS KEPT: rsLength, rsSlopeLen, rsLevelLen, rsSlopeThresh.
// Note: rsSlopeThresh may need slight tuning — JdK RS-Ratio swings wider
// than Mansfield, so the "Rising/Declining" label triggers more sensitively.
//
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.3.0 — DECISION-MODE COMPRESSION + DETAILED-VIEW TOGGLE
// ==========================================
// PRINCIPLE: 70+ fields was too many for a trade decision. v67.3.0 collapses
//   the dashboard into 13–18 composite rows organised by decision-rank
//   (Act Now → Structure → Context → Portfolio → Alpha Screener). No
//   information is lost — every detail from the previous version is preserved
//   inside the composite cells via dense one-liner encodings.
//
// NEW INPUT (group "Dashboard Style"):
//   show_detailed_view (default: false)
//     OFF (Decision Mode)   → 13–18 composite rows. Default. Use for trading.
//     ON  (Detailed Mode)   → ~60 raw rows. Use for debugging / tuning.
//
// COMPOSITE ROWS (Decision Mode):
//   🎯 ACT NOW       — Recommendation · Action Signal · Catalyst+Gates · Asset Quality
//   📊 STRUCTURE     — Weekly Structure · Daily Structure · Price Action · Momentum · Levels/Room
//   🌐 CONTEXT       — Macro/Sector · RS (Mansfield) · Style/Persona
//   📦 PORTFOLIO     — Portfolio Health · My Trade · Position Status  (only when position open)
//   ⚡ ALPHA SCREENER — Top 5 watchlist setups
//
// MERGER MAP (each composite cell preserves the underlying detail):
//   WEEKLY STRUCTURE  ← Market Structure + Stage 2 Age + Master Trend + Price>30WMA + 30WMA Slope + Weekly PB Health
//   DAILY STRUCTURE   ← Daily Trend + Trend Engine + Trend Template + Price>50DMA + 50DMA Slope
//   MOMENTUM          ← RSI + Divergence + Volume Trend + Volatility (ADR) + EMA20 Proximity + Pullback Health
//   LEVELS / ROOM     ← Overhead Resist + Room for Trade + 52W Space + ATH Space + Key-Level Proximity
//   MACRO / SECTOR    ← Mkt Health (N500) + Sector Info + Sector Stage + Sector Velocity + Next Earnings
//   RS (Mansfield)    ← RS500 + RS Sector + RRG Quadrant (RS Nifty 50 dropped — N500 is canonical breadth)
//   CATALYST + GATES  ← Catalyst code + POS-BO 9-gate bracket + names of failing gates
//   MY TRADE          ← Trade status + Current R:R + Dynamic Profile
//   POSITION STATUS   ← Entry Date + Days Held + Time Stop warning
//   STYLE / PERSONA   ← Trade Style + Persona
//
// LOGIC UNCHANGED: every internal score, catalyst, gate, and detector continues
//   to compute exactly as before. Only the display layer changes. Toggle ON
//   to verify any composite cell against its underlying rows.
//
// HELPERS ADDED: f_rrg_quad / f_rrg_quad_letter (RRG quadrant classification
//   from Mansfield level + 4-bar momentum — Dashboard's canonical engine,
//   not the Bull Screener variant).
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.5 — BULL SCREENER AS CANONICAL CATALYST REFERENCE

// ============================================================================
//  STRICT-TREND ENGINE — ARCHITECTURAL CONTRACT (v67.2.4)
// ============================================================================
//  The canonical source of truth for HH / HL / LH / LL classification and the
//  derived trend state is the **Zigzag [Strict] indicator (v6.2)** — NOT this
//  Dashboard. The functions f_classifyHigh / f_classifyLow / f_getStrictTrend
//  below are a **mirror** of Zigzag's internals and must remain bit-identical
//  to it. If Zigzag's strict engine changes, this file MUST be updated to
//  match — no independent evolution.
//
//  Canonical defaults (must match the on-chart Zigzag):
//    • Engine version    : v6.2
//    • Pivot Left/Right  : 2 / 2 (daily); 5 / 5 (weekly, hard-coded)
//    • EH/EL threshold   : 0.005 (0.5 %)
//
//  If a user overrides any of these inputs without making the same change in
//  the on-chart Zigzag panel, the Dashboard's "Trend Engine" row turns ORANGE
//  to flag the drift.
// ============================================================================

// ============================================================================
//  CATALYST ENGINE — ARCHITECTURAL CONTRACT (v67.2.5)
// ============================================================================
//  The canonical source of truth for catalyst detection (POS-ACCUM, POS-BO,
//  SWG-BO, SWG-PB, SWG-GAP, SWG-REV) is the **Commander Bull Screener v2.9**
//  indicator — NOT this Dashboard. The catalyst engine in section 8 below is
//  a verbatim port of Bull Screener lines 942–1096, including the full 9-gate
//  weinstein_setup stack, alpha_ok / hunter_adx_ok / hunter_weekly_rsi_min
//  numeric gates, minervini_trend template, and the priority cascade.
//
//  Mirror version target  : Commander_Bull_Screener_v2.9.pine
//  Canonical defaults     : hunter_weekly_rsi_min=60, hunter_daily_adx_min=25,
//                           pos_accum_rsi_max=50, vol_acc_min=3
//
//  If the Bull Screener's catalyst logic changes, this file MUST be updated
//  to match — no independent evolution. Cite the Screener commit / version
//  in the changelog when porting changes.
// ============================================================================

// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.5 — BULL SCREENER AS CANONICAL CATALYST REFERENCE
// ==========================================
// ARCHITECTURAL: The Dashboard's catalyst engine is now formally treated as
//   a MIRROR of the Commander Bull Screener v2.9 catalyst stack. The header
//   block above captures the contract; future edits to the gate / catalyst
//   logic must be propagated FROM the Bull Screener, never originated here.
//   Same principle and same maintenance flow as the v67.2.4 trend mirror.
//
// REWRITE: Catalyst engine (section 8) rewritten as a verbatim port of
//   Commander_Bull_Screener_v2.9.pine lines 942–1096. New gate stack:
//     G1 Stage 2/1            G6 Vol Accum (≥3 of last 20)
//     G2 Price > 200 MA       G7 Stage 2 macro freshness ≤ 26w
//     G3 Sector RS not Lagging  G8 SMA20/50 squeeze ≤ 5%
//     G4 Sector Stage 1/2     G9 BB squeeze (width < 30-bar SMA)
//     G5 Trend Template (≤25% from 52WH, ≥30% from 52WL)
//   Catalyst priority cascade now matches the Screener exactly:
//     POS-ACCUM → POS-BO → SWG-GAP → SWG-BO → SWG-PB → SWG-REV → NONE.
//   Old Dashboard's permissive catalyst patterns (Stage 2 + EMA proximity only)
//   are replaced. SWG-PB tightened from ±5% → ±1.5% EMA distance (matching
//   Screener). All six catalysts now require alpha_ok (Asset Quality ≥ 60)
//   except POS-BO/SWG-GAP which use weinstein_setup (which itself contains
//   alpha-equivalent gates).
//
// NEW INPUTS (group "Bull Screener Mirror"):
//   hunter_weekly_rsi_min  (default 60) — POS-BO weekly RSI floor
//   hunter_daily_adx_min   (default 25) — POS-BO daily ADX floor
//   pos_accum_rsi_max      (default 50) — POS-ACCUM daily RSI ceiling
//   vol_acc_min_bs         (default 3)  — Screener-aligned vol-accum density
//   All defaults exactly match Commander Bull Screener v2.9 input defaults.
//
// NEW ROW: "POS-BO Gates" rendered directly below "CATALYST (Edge)" — shows
//   "X/9 [1234·6789]" where each digit is the gate number (· if failing).
//   GREEN when 9/9 (POS-BO eligible), ORANGE 6-8, RED < 6. Direct mirror of
//   the Bull Screener's POS-BO GATES panel.
//
// DAILY BUNDLE: Added d_l52 (ta.lowest(low, 252)) for the trend-template gate.
//
// SIDE EFFECTS: The old `is_stg2`, `is_stg1`, `v_dry`, `vcp_tg`, `cf_flat`,
//   `c_obv*`, `c_rsi70`, `c_h10_1`, `c_rsi3`, `c_h250_1`, `c_p_h50` variables
//   are removed (only used by the old catalyst block). `anti_algo_ok` and
//   `_intraday_pos` are preserved (still used by the "Anti-Algo BO Gate" row).
//   The PA-cascade's own `isBreakout` and `hitPullback` are unchanged; the
//   Screener-aligned versions live as `bs_isBreakout` and `bs_hitPullback`.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.4 — ZIGZAG AS CANONICAL TREND REFERENCE
// ==========================================
// ARCHITECTURAL: The strict-trend engine in this file is now formally treated
//   as a MIRROR of the on-chart Zigzag [Strict v6.2] indicator. The header
//   block above captures the contract; future edits to f_getStrictTrend must
//   be propagated FROM Zigzag, never originated here.
// NEW : "Trend Engine" row added to the dashboard right-column header. Renders
//   "v6.2 · L<n>/R<n> · X.X%" (engine version · pivot · eq_threshold). Cell is
//   GREEN when all three knobs match canonical Zigzag defaults (v6.2, 2/2,
//   0.5%) and ORANGE when any knob is overridden — a visible warning that the
//   user must apply the same override to the Zigzag panel to keep agreement.
// DOC : Guide §14 rewritten to formalize the architectural principle ("Zigzag
//   is the source of truth; Dashboard mirrors") with explicit drift-detection
//   procedure and engine-version maintenance rules.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.3 — DAILY-TREND CROSS-TOOL ALIGNMENT
// ==========================================
// REVERT: Daily pivot defaults rolled back from 3/3 → 2/2.
//   Rationale: v67.2.1 FIX #13 bumped these from 2/2 to 3/3 hoping to reduce
//   strict-trend noise. Side-effect: Dashboard "Daily Trend" disagreed with
//   the on-chart Zigzag [Strict v6.x] panel (which defaults to 2/2). Both
//   tools share the same v6.2 strict-trend engine, but different pivot
//   windows detect different swings — so the disagreement was purely a
//   settings-default mismatch, not an algorithmic divergence.
//   v67.2.3 restores 2/2 as the default so out-of-the-box the two tools
//   agree. Users who want the smoother 3/3 view can still set it via input.
// TOOLTIP: pivotLeft / pivotRight tooltips now flag the "must match on-chart
//   Zigzag" dependency loudly, so future tuning doesn't silently desync.
// DOC : Guide §14 added — "Cross-Tool Trend Alignment Checklist" covering
//   pivot settings, eq_threshold, and engine version.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.2 — STAGE 2 AGE DISAMBIGUATION
// ==========================================
// Resolves the long-standing display mismatch between three different "Stage 2"
// duration numbers reported by different tools:
//   • Dashboard's old "(12w)"  — sub-stage leg age (resets on UP↔PULLBACK)
//   • Commander Bull Screener "(47w)" — macro Stage-2 lifespan
//   • Unified Ecosystem "Fresh" tag    — categorical freshness flag
// All three were computed correctly; they measured DIFFERENT things sharing the
// same label. This release surfaces both anchors side-by-side.
//
// NEW   : f_getStageAndTime now tracks a second anchor `macroStart` that only
//         resets when the stage family EXITS Stage 2 entirely (not on internal
//         UP↔PULLBACK transitions). Bubbled through the weekly super-bundle
//         tuple as `stageMacroStart`.
// NEW   : Dashboard row "Stage 2 Age" added directly below "Market Structure".
//         Format: "<leg>w leg / <macro>w macro · <Fresh|Maturing|Extended>".
//           Fresh     = leg ≤ stage2_fresh_weeks (default 13w)
//           Maturing  = leg > threshold, macro ≤ 26w
//           Extended  = macro > 26w
// CHANGE: "Market Structure" cell no longer appends "(Xw)" — week count now
//         lives in the dedicated "Stage 2 Age" row, giving regime and timing
//         their own glance-zones.
// INPUT : New "Stage 2 'Fresh' Threshold (weeks)" added to the Advanced
//         Thresholds group. Default 13, range 4-52.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2.1 — DEFERRED FIXES PASS
// ==========================================
// FIX #4 : POWER PLAY (Strong Close) promoted from B-tier (+1) to A-tier (+2)
//          and moved above breakout/consolidation branches in the cascade.
//          Old branch order meant a long bullish lower-wick bar was suppressed
//          when price happened to be near dLockH (the consolidation branch
//          would match first). Now: a true strong-close candle is always
//          recognised on its own merits.
// FIX #6 : "Volume Profile" label/comment renamed to "Max-Vol Bar (POC proxy)".
//          The c_vp metric picks the HIGH of the highest-volume bar in
//          vpLookback — useful as a recent-institutional-interest proxy but
//          NOT a true POC. Logic unchanged; label now agrees with logic.
// FIX #7 : SMC Liquidity Sweep (c_liq_sweep) now has a configurable bar-lockout
//          guard (default 10 bars). Old logic re-fired every bar where conditions
//          held, producing repeat "LIQ SWEEP RECLAIM" prints during normal
//          pullbacks. New: fires once, suppresses for liq_sweep_lockout bars.
// FIX #14: 9 hard-coded thresholds promoted to proper user inputs under a new
//          "Advanced Thresholds" group:
//            vol_acc_days, vol_acc_min, vol_avg_len, vcp_thresh, vdu_pct,
//            eq_threshold_dash, prox_thresh, pb_dist_max, liq_sweep_lockout.
//          Defaults preserved; tooltips added.
// NOTE #11: Action Signal color thresholds (≥7 green, ≥4 orange) were already
//          retuned in the v67.2 enhancement pass — no further action.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2 — ENHANCEMENT PASS
// ==========================================
// NEW   : PRICE ACTION STRUCTURE — expanded from 7 → 22 setups, organised into
//         tiers that feed a single integer `paTier` (range -2…+4):
//           A++ (+4) : ★★ POWER PLAY (HTF)
//           A+  (+3) : ★ SPRING (Failed Breakdown), ★ VCP BREAKOUT, ★ STAGE-2 LAUNCH
//           A   (+2) : BREAKOUT (Confirmed), ★ POCKET PIVOT, ★ LIQ SWEEP RECLAIM,
//                      BULLISH ENGULFING, 3-BAR REVERSAL (Bull)
//           B   (+1) : BREAKOUT (Unconfirmed), CONSOLIDATION (Tight), FLAT BASE,
//                      INSIDE-3, ★ TRUE NR7, INSIDE BAR, POWER PLAY (Strong Close),
//                      HAMMER (Reversal)
//           0   ( 0) : NORMAL
//           C   (-1) : SELLING TAIL (Rejection)
//           D   (-2) : ⚠️ FAILED BREAKOUT, DISTRIBUTION DAY, BEARISH ENGULFING
//         Resolves Bug #1: VCP signal now reaches paState (was computed but only
//         consumed by the Catalyst engine — never the composite scores).
// NEW   : ACTION SIGNAL coupled to PA. Old 7-star scale dropped. Score is now
//         numerical (0–10) with a qualitative label:
//           action_score = clamp(raw_conf_score + paTier, 0, 10)
//         where raw_conf_score is 0–6 booleans (Trend, Mom, Vol, VP, ADX,
//         LiqSweep). The trivial `c_pa = close > open` factor is dropped —
//         paTier now provides the PA evidence at proper resolution.
//         Display: "X/10 (Label)" — Label: Weak / Moderate / Good / Strong / Excellent.
//         Resolves Bug #5: PA evidence finally feeds the Action Signal.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.2 — BUG FIX PASS
// ==========================================
// FIX #2  : NR7 detection. Old code (`range < ATR14 * 0.5`) was a "narrow-range bar"
//           heuristic, NOT a true NR7. Replaced with strict NR7: current bar range
//           is the smallest of the last 7 bars (label now reads "★ TRUE NR7").
// FIX #3  : Price-Action cascade was gated by `if not na(dLockH)`. When dLockH was
//           na (early bars or symbols without a recent daily pivot high), paState
//           stayed stuck at "INSIDE RANGE" and downstream consumers (sw_pat_ok)
//           never saw a valid setup. Cascade now runs every bar; each branch that
//           needs dLockH carries its own `not na(dLockH)` guard.
// FIX #8  : AVWAP block previously made a 2nd `request.security` for
//           f_getStageAndTime to fetch _st — duplicating the call already made
//           at line 1771 (which exposes `stageStart` globally). Now reuses the
//           pre-fetched `stageStart`. Saves 1 of the 40 request.security budget.
// FIX #9  : AVWAP init race — `var int last_anchor_time = 0` made `time >= 0`
//           always true on bar 0, so cumVol/cumVolPrice accumulated from epoch
//           until the first stage change. Fixed by initialising last_anchor_time
//           to `na`-equivalent (sentinel = 1) and only accumulating when
//           `last_anchor_time > 1` (i.e. a real anchor has been set).
// FIX #10 : FVG demand/supply zones (last_dz / last_sz) were `var` and never
//           invalidated. Old gaps remained "active" forever even after price had
//           clearly violated them. Now invalidated when close penetrates the zone.
// FIX #15 : Asset Quality score could go negative (under-performance branch
//           subtracts 10 with no floor). Added `math.max(0, score)` floor before
//           the upper cap.
// TUNE #13: Daily-pivot defaults bumped from 2/2 → 3/3 (less twitchy strict
//           trend; weekly still uses hard-coded 5/5). User can override.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.1
// ==========================================
// SYNC: f_getStrictTrend engine propagated to match Zigzag [Strict v6.2] fixes:
// FIX: eq_threshold in f_classifyHigh/f_classifyLow raised from 0.1% to 0.5%
//   (matches Zigzag default; avoids false EH/EL on instruments with minor pivot noise).
// FIX: Extension path (Section 1/2) now re-classifies against prevLockedHigh/
//   prevLockedLow instead of lockedHigh/lockedLow — fixes false HH/LL classification
//   when an extending pivot overshoots the current direction's initial lock price.
// FIX: f_updateTrend gate: EL no longer confirms uptrend (HH+HL strict only);
//   EH no longer confirms downtrend (LL+LH strict only). EH/EL always → SIDEWAYS.
// FIX: Section 3 opposite-side classification now reads confirmed lastLowClass/
//   lastHighClass directly instead of re-classifying from projSync — prevents
//   structural mismatch between projection and confirmed pivot states.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v67.0
// ==========================================
// - CLEANUP: Removed the Recovery Edges detection panel (REV-CB, REV-RS, REV-EARLY)
//   and the RFF Lite fundamental gate. All recovery logic is now fully handled by
//   the Weinstein Unified Ecosystem (Unified Strategy) indicator.
// - REMOVED: 'Recovery Edges' input group (9 inputs).
// - REMOVED: f_getStrictTrendDash(), rolling-extremes block, 3-way regime gate,
//   4-pillar CB detection, REV-RS logic, REV-EARLY logic, and RFF Lite
//   (2 request.financial calls). Pine call budget -2 financial calls.
// - The table placeholder comment at row 3831 now cleanly separates the
//   existing right-column Technical block from the Alpha Screener.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v65.0
// ==========================================
// - REORGANIZATION: Restructured the dashboard table logic to follow a true top-down approach.
// - Left Column flows from Macro & Sector -> Asset Quality -> Action/Setup -> Portfolio Management.
// - Right Column flows from Positional (Weekly) -> Swing (Daily) -> Alpha Screener.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v64.0
// ==========================================
// - NEW: Recovery Edges detection panel — ports REV-CB (4-pillar capitulation
//   bottom), REV-RS (RS survivor breakout, strict-trend gated), and REV-EARLY
//   (NR7/inside-3 + 20-bar reclaim) from Weinstein Recovery Strategy v1.4 /
//   Capitulation Screener v1.3. 5-bar signal hold window (var int last_*_bar).
// - NEW: 3-way recovery regime gate — mkt_idx_corrected (≥7% off CNX500 52W
//   high) OR mkt_reclaim (CNX500 close > SMA50 within 30 bars) OR stock_corrected
//   (≥10% off own 52W high). Reuses the existing bench500 security call —
//   extended to also return CNX500 52W high (no new security call).
// - NEW: RFF Lite fundamental gate — 2 request.financial calls (NET_INCOME TTM,
//   CASH_F_OPERATING_ACTIVITIES TTM). Score 0-2. When require_rff_lite is on
//   and score < 2, BUY/STRONG-BUY recommendations are downgraded to "BUY*"
//   (technical signal fired but fundamentals failed).
// - NEW: f_getStrictTrend helper (port from v1.4 strategy) — pivot-based
//   HH/HL trend detector used by REV-RS gate.
// - NEW: Dashboard panel rows — "RECOVERY" section showing 4-pillar dot grid
//   (●●●● colour-coded), active edge label (REV-CB/REV-RS/REV-EARLY/NONE),
//   regime status (MKT-CORR/RECLAIM/STOCK-CORR/OFF), recovery score, and
//   RFF Lite (2/2 ✓ | 1/2 ⚠ | 0/2 ✗).
// - Inputs: new "Recovery Edges" group (enable, drawdown %, red-bar count,
//   range lookback, min correction %, hold window, require_rff_lite).
// - Pine call budget: +0 request.security, +2 request.financial. Fully reuses
//   existing CNX500 / Mansfield calls.
// ==========================================
// CHANGELOG v63.4
// ==========================================
// - Mansfield RS rescaled to ×100 (RRG-compatible: RS-Ratio ≈ mansfield + 100).
//   Ratio symbol "STOCK / BENCH" remains the input source — `close` inside the
//   security call IS stock_close / bench_close (benchmark-relative by construction).
// - Three weekly RS request.security calls switched from lookahead_on → lookahead_off
//   to remove forward-bar bias.
// - 130-bar warm-up gate on Mansfield to suppress junk RS during early history.
// - True RRG quadrants derived from (mansfield, RS-momentum=ROC(mansfield,4)):
//   LEADING / WEAKENING / LAGGING / IMPROVING. f_rrg_color/icon updated to take
//   the quadrant string instead of slope.
// - SWG-GAP catalyst now requires intra-bar pos >= 0.60 (anti-algo), mirroring
//   v4.52 strategy gate — eliminates gap-and-crap reversals.
// - rsSlopeThresh default rescaled 0.02 → 0.2 (and velocity thresholds ×10) to
//   match new ×100 Mansfield scale.
// ==========================================

